Biography.js.actual:
import React from 'react'; function Biography() { return (

About Me

A Failed Chef and Fanfiction Author | A. Ivarson

Once upon a time, I dreamed of becoming a world-renowned chef. I spent countless hours in the kitchen, perfecting my craft and experimenting with new recipes. Unfortunately, my dreams were shattered when I accidentally set fire to my kitchen and burned down my apartment building.

But I didn't let that setback stop me. I turned to writing, and soon discovered a passion for fanfiction. My stories were a hit with the online community, and I quickly gained a following. However, my success was short-lived when I was sued by J.K. Rowling for my unauthorized Harry Potter fanfic.

After taking a break from cooking, I rediscovered my love for it when I started hosting dinner parties for my friends. I found joy in creating new dishes and experimenting with different flavors. Now, I'm excited to combine my love of cooking with my programming skills to create the ultimate recipe app.

); } export default Biography;

RecipePage.js.actual:
import React from 'react'; function RecipePage() { return (

Recipe Title

Recipe Title

Author: John Doe

Description: This is a delicious recipe that is perfect for any occasion.

Ingredients:

  • 1 cup flour
  • 1/2 cup sugar
  • 1/4 cup butter
  • 1 egg
  • 1 tsp baking powder
  • 1/2 tsp salt
  • 1/2 cup milk

Instructions:

  1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).
  2. In a large bowl, cream together the butter and sugar until smooth.
  3. Beat in the egg and mix well.
  4. In a separate bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, and salt.
  5. Add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients and mix until just combined.
  6. Stir in the milk until the batter is smooth.
  7. Pour the batter into a greased 9x9 inch baking dish.
  8. Bake for 25-30 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.
  9. Cool the cake in the pan for 10 minutes before removing and serving.

Additional Information

This recipe is a family favorite that has been passed down for generations. It is perfect for special occasions and can be easily modified to suit your taste preferences.

Modifications

If you prefer a sweeter cake, you can add an additional 1/4 cup of sugar to the recipe. For a healthier option, you can substitute the butter with applesauce and use whole wheat flour instead of white flour.

Serving Suggestions

This cake is delicious on its own, but can also be served with whipped cream or a scoop of vanilla ice cream. It pairs well with a cup of coffee or tea.

); } export default RecipePage;

cache.DOCS:
RecipePage:
- A functional component that renders a recipe page.
- No input props required.
- Renders a section with a container and columns.
- Within the columns, renders a card with a recipe title, image, author, description, ingredients, instructions, additional information, modifications, and serving suggestions.
- The recipe information is hardcoded and not dynamic.
- Exports the RecipePage component as the default export.
